In view of the above observations, we have recommended the following:

Ensure that all Driver’s Trip Ticket are properly filled out, numbered and recorded in a logbook for control purposes. A separate file of Driver’s Trip Ticket per vehicle must be maintained;

The municipality shall submit to the COA Audit Team Monthly Reports of Official Travels and Monthly Reports of Official Fuel Consumption for audit purposes at the end of every month;

Refrain from issuing gasoline and diesel to officials who are receiving Transportation Allowance;

Government vehicles shall only be utilized for official business trip, with the nature of the travel completely disclosed therein.

Recommendations:
In view of the above observations, we have recommended the following:
Ensure that all Driver’s Trip Ticket are properly filled out, numbered and recorded in a logbook for control purposes. A separate file of Driver’s Trip Ticket per vehicle must be maintained;
The municipality shall submit to the COA Audit Team Monthly Reports of Official Travels and Monthly Reports of Official Fuel Consumption for audit purposes at the end of every month;
Refrain from issuing gasoline and diesel to officials who are receiving Transportation Allowance;
Government vehicles shall only be utilized for official business trip, with the nature of the travel completely disclosed therein.

We have recommended that Management observe the following in compliance with RA No. 9003:

The Municipality must adopt a systematic, comprehensive and ecological solid waste management program in accordance with the Municipal Solid Waste Management Plan;

Strictly enforce existing Municipal Ordinances and strategies relative to solid waste management to ensure compliance with segregation at source; 

Involve the participation of barangays for information dissemination and of proper garbage disposal; and

Initial conversion of the open dumpsite to a controlled dumpsite.

Recommendation:
